How to install:

0. Prereq: install and configure HBase 0.92 in pseudo distributed mode

1. build htx jar
  cd ${HTX_HOME}
  mvn install

2. copy jar to HBase installation
  cp target/htx-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar ${HBASE_HOME}/lib/

3. build htx test jar
  mvn jar:test-jar

4. copy test jar to HBase installation
  cp target/htx-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT-tests.jar ${HBASE_HOME}/lib/

5. edit hbase-site.xml to configure HTX coprocessor:

  <property>
    <name>hbase.coprocessor.region.classes</name>
    <value>edu.illinois.htx.regionserver.HRegionTransactionManager</value>
    <description>Installs the HTX coprocessor</description>
  </property>

6. start HDFS
  cd ${HADOOP_HOME}
  bin/start-dfs.sh

7. start HBase
  cd ${HBASE_HOME}
  bin/start-hbase.sh

// skip this step right now, the client is hacked to generate time-stamps
// 8. start time-stamp oracle (open new shell since process blocks)
//  bin/hbase edu.illinois.htx.tso.TimestampOracleServer

9. create test table
  bin/hbase shell
  > create 'account', 'balance'
  > exit

10. run test case
  bin/hbase edu.illinois.htx.client.SingleTableTest
  (last printed line should be: 'succeeded')

11. check account table
  bin/hbase shell
  > scan 'account', {VERIONS => 3}
  (should print four cells: two for each row; one with timestamp=0, one with timestamp=1)
